"Espinosa" depicts the battle of Espinosa de los Monteros on November 10th and 11th, 1808.  Fought high in the Cantabrian mountains in Northern Spain, between Lt-Gen Blake&rsquo;s Army of Galicia and Marshal Victor&rsquo;s I Corps. The battle was fought during Napoleon&rsquo;s massive second invasion of Spain and although Blake&rsquo;s starved troops fought the victors of Friedland to a standstill it was all in vain, as the Army of Galicia could not escape the jaws of Napoleon&rsquo;s grand plan.

